    <title>Carbon Pollution Transparency Act</title>
    <createDate>2017-07-19T03:11:33Z</createDate>
    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <actionDate>2017-07-18</actionDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2017-07-28T18:39:25Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <updateDate>2017-07-18T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Carbon Pollution Transparency Act </b></p> <p> This bill requires the Congressional Budget Office (CBO) to calculate a carbon score for legislation. The carbon score is the projected net greenhouse gas emissions that would result from: (1) enactment and implementation of a bill or resolution, and (2) the appropriation of any amounts authorized in the legislation. </p> <p>The CBO must include the carbon score in cost estimates for reported legislation that are submitted to congressional committees pursuant to the Congressional Budget Act of 1974. </p>]]></text>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
